item.summary: Some ws tests fail with security manager

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment:
The proposed fix has been discussed with Alessio. The Service Ref test-cases need extra permissions for their deployments because CXF guys are not willing to add more privileged blocks into CXF codebase. These extra permissions are aligned to the current JBossWS-CXF testsuite, see [1].

The proposed fix, however, needs additional fix in JAXWS SPI, see JBEE-162.

Note: a potential fix for all these perms in CXF can be seen at [2].

[1] https://github.com/jbossws/jbossws-cxf/blob/master/modules/testsuite/shared-tests/src/test/resources/jaxws/samples/serviceref/META-INF/permissions.xml

[2] https://github.com/istudens/cxf/commit/899120496592e7208429eb36014814e6d85b62f4
WSDL4J permission issue is tracked by WFLY-3463.
Re-opening for additional fix required by QE.
